This README file contains information on the contents of the meta-emsyslabs layer.


Installation
============

* Get the yocto scarthgap
    mkdir yocto-scarthgap
    cd yocto-scarthgap
    repo init -u https://github.com/SoMLabs/imx-meta-somlabs -b scarthgap -m imx-somlabs-6.6.23-2.0.0.xml
    repo sync

* Change directory to sources dir 
    cd imx-meta-somlabs/sources
* Clone emsyslabs layer into the source dir:
    git clone https://github.com/lucckb/yoctosom-meta-emsyslabs.git meta-emsyslabs
* Add following entry into the configuration file imx-somlabs-setup-release.sh
   at line 180:
    echo "BBLAYERS += \"\${BSPDIR}/sources/meta-emsyslabs\"" >> $BUILD_DIR/conf/bblayers.conf
* Run the configuration script:
    DISTRO=somlabs-xwayland MACHINE=spacesom-8mplus-cb source imx-somlabs-setup-release.sh -b build-spacesom-8mplus-cb-imx
* build yocto image bitbake somlabs-image


Libcamera tests
=======
* Connect ov5640 camera to the MIPI-CSI1
* List available cameras:
    cam -l 
* Try to capture some frames
    LIBCAMERA_LOG_LEVELS=*:DEBUG cam -c 1 --capture=10
* Display video on the screen using libcamera and gst
    gst-launch-1.0 libcamerasrc camera-name="/base/soc\@0/bus\@30800000/i2c\@30a20000/ov5640\@3c" ! queue ! glimagesink

